Package: DreamAI2
Type: Package
Title: DreamAI2: An Imputation Tool for Data-Independent Acquisition
        Proteomics Data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Weiping Ma, Jessica Ren, Sunkyu Kim, Shrabanti Chowdhury, Zhi Li, Thomas Yu, Mi Yang, 
  Francesca Petralia, Jeremy Jacobsen, Jingyi Jessica Li, Xinzhou Ge, Kexin Li, Nathan Edwards, 
  Samuel Payne, Henry Rodriguez, Paul Boutros, Gustavo Stolovitzky, Jaewoo Kang, David Fenyo, 
  Julio Saez-Rodriguez, Pei Wang
Maintainer: Weiping Ma <weiping.ma@mssm.edu>, Jessica Ren<jessicaqren@gmail.com>
Description: The function imputes the missing protein abundances in a protein-sample matrix 
  using individual or ensemble output from 7 methods. 
  The 7 methods include K-nearest neighbor (KNN), 
  Nonparametric Missing Value Imputation using Random Forest (MissForest), 
  Abundance Dependent Missing Imputation (ADMIN), 
  Iteratively Reweighted Nuclear Norm (IRNN) algorithm with SCAD penalty (Brinn), 
  Matrix factorization algorithm to obtain latent parameters of proteins and samples with MCMC algorithm used for the optimization (SpectroFM), 
  a flexible, iterative, regression based imputation approach (RegImpute) 
  and Multivariate Imputation by Chained Equations (MICE). 
